1
00:00:07,108 --> 00:00:10,177
⟨I spent days full of love with 50 people who love me →

2
00:00:10,211 --> 00:00:12,179
Detective Manami Tanizaki⟩

3
00:00:12,213 --> 00:00:15,716
⟨An incident occurred in which Manami's My Love was killed one after another⟩

4
00:00:16,050 --> 00:00:19,487
⟨Behind the scenes is a mastermind who calls himself “Ai-chan”⟩

5
00:00:19,553 --> 00:00:23,057
(Kuroiwa) 10 people? (Manami) Everyone... My love.

6
00:00:25,559 --> 00:00:27,495
(Kuroiwa) Mr. Kiyosumi! (Kiyosumi) What?

7
00:00:27,561 --> 00:00:29,497
(Kuroiwa) Manami-san, be careful...

8
00:00:29,563 --> 00:00:31,499
(Kiyosumi) The guy who is doing it with all the victims →

9
00:00:31,565 --> 00:00:34,502
There's no way I'll let you work, you idiot.

10
00:00:34,568 --> 00:00:36,570
(Kuroiwa) Huh…｡ 📱(Vibration sound)

11
00:00:40,074 --> 00:00:41,509
(Kuroiwa) What!? (Kiyosumi) What happened?

12
00:00:41,575 --> 00:00:43,511
(Kuroiwa) No, not at all... it's okay.

13
00:00:43,577 --> 00:00:45,513
>> What? (Kuroiwa) No, no... please read.

14
00:00:45,579 --> 00:00:48,516
>> I feel bad... (Kuroiwa) I'm coming!

15
00:00:48,582 --> 00:00:50,518
(Sound of hitting desk) (Kuroiwa) It hurt!

16
00:00:50,584 --> 00:00:53,020
It's cold!

17
00:00:53,087 --> 00:00:55,089
Huh?

18
00:01:02,096 --> 00:01:03,964
(Erasaki) There's nothing quite like this.

19
00:01:04,031 --> 00:01:06,967
(Erasaki) Drink, you? You drink, hey.

20
00:01:07,034 --> 00:01:09,470
(Emoto) Huh... (Erasaki) Huh? Why do I need it?

21
00:01:09,537 --> 00:01:11,972
You, drink this, you... >> \I won't drink it/

22
00:01:12,039 --> 00:01:14,475
(Erasaki) Drink! You're so boring.

23
00:01:14,542 --> 00:01:16,477
Hey, I'm here again!

24
00:01:16,544 --> 00:01:18,479
(Erasaki) Hona, how about a welcome drink?

25
00:01:18,546 --> 00:01:20,481
(Kuroiwa) That's fine... >> Don't hold back, dear.

26
00:01:20,548 --> 00:01:22,483
(Kuroiwa) It's okay... >> Just say it, this is it...

27
00:01:22,550 --> 00:01:24,552
Huh? (Kuroiwa) No, no…｡

28
00:01:30,057 --> 00:01:32,993
(Erasaki) Wow~ Yeah, it looks like a drinking cup.

29
00:01:33,060 --> 00:01:35,996
(Emoto) Sake cups are not something to be exchanged easily.

30
00:01:36,063 --> 00:01:37,998
(Kuroiwa) Huh…｡

31
00:01:38,065 --> 00:01:41,001
(Manami) Ah~ Thank you everyone for coming.

32
00:01:41,068 --> 00:01:44,505
(Erasaki) Oh~ Manami-chan, it's been a while. (Manami) It's been a while.

33
00:01:44,572 --> 00:01:46,073
(Erasaki) Hey...!

34
00:01:49,076 --> 00:01:50,511
(Manami) Ku~!

35
00:01:50,578 --> 00:01:53,013
(Kuroiwa) Um... these people...

36
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:55,015
(Manami) Everyone, my love.

37
00:01:55,082 --> 00:01:56,517
♪～

38
00:01:56,584 --> 00:02:00,020
(Kuroiwa) Ahhh, I thought so!!

39
00:02:00,087 --> 00:02:05,459
♪～

40
00:02:05,526 --> 00:02:10,464
(Manami) As I informed you, everyone in My Love is being killed one by one.

41
00:02:10,531 --> 00:02:13,968
In fact, 12 people have already died.

42
00:02:14,034 --> 00:02:17,471
(buzz)

43
00:02:17,538 --> 00:02:21,141
(Manami) Somehow, I wanted to protect everyone, so I asked them to come together.

44
00:02:21,175 --> 00:02:24,478
(Wanibuchi: Loudly) This is the "last stronghold"...?

45
00:02:24,545 --> 00:02:26,981
Eh, is the volume of your voice correct? >> Ha, excuse me.

46
00:02:27,047 --> 00:02:30,484
I couldn't get over the role of Gokusaimaru in the musical ``Jet Black Shadow Shinobi.''

47
00:02:30,551 --> 00:02:33,053
Wow, you're a celebrity! Amazing!

48
00:02:37,558 --> 00:02:40,494
(Manami) And he's my colleague detective Kuroiwa-kun.

49
00:02:40,561 --> 00:02:42,496
(Kuroiwa) Ah... hello.

50
00:02:42,563 --> 00:02:45,566
(Amit) Colleague? Aren't you supposed to stay out of it?

51
00:02:47,067 --> 00:02:50,504
(Manami) Ah, he's really just a colleague.

52
00:02:50,571 --> 00:02:52,006
Not my love.

53
00:02:52,072 --> 00:02:55,509
(Kuroiwa) Well... well, that's right.

54
00:02:55,576 --> 00:02:58,012
(Manami) I was thinking of asking him to guard me tonight.

55
00:02:58,078 --> 00:02:59,580
(Kuroiwa) Yes?

56
00:03:05,019 --> 00:03:07,955
(EITO) Sorry, I finally finished work.

57
00:03:08,022 --> 00:03:09,957
(Kuroiwa) It's Koi Ria.

58
00:03:10,024 --> 00:03:11,959
(Manami) E-chan.

59
00:03:12,026 --> 00:03:14,028
>> This is EITO from SATURDAY. Nice to meet you!

60
00:03:15,529 --> 00:03:17,965
Wow! What a serious celebrity!

61
00:03:18,032 --> 00:03:19,967
Aura is terrible!

62
00:03:20,034 --> 00:03:23,037
(Kuroiwa) Huh... No, I'm getting confused.

63
00:03:24,038 --> 00:03:25,539
(Manami) Wow...｡

64
00:03:27,041 --> 00:03:30,477
>>Okay! Let's go to bed right away. (Manami) Ah, no, no, no.

65
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:33,480
>> Huh? (Manami) Until I solve the case →

66
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:35,482
I don't do it with anyone.

67
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:40,487
If the culprit is caught, I'll definitely do it again.

68
00:03:40,554 --> 00:03:42,990
(Kuroiwa) Huh? Am I the only one who doesn't understand?

69
00:03:43,057 --> 00:03:44,992
(Manami) Well then, security please.

70
00:03:45,059 --> 00:03:47,494
(Kuroiwa) No, what is this place anyway?

71
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:50,497
(Manami) This is a pension reserved for everyone.

72
00:03:50,564 --> 00:03:52,499
(Kuroiwa) Huh? (Manami) The future will be like this →

73
00:03:52,566 --> 00:03:56,003
I want to gather everyone from My Love and build a nursing home.

74
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:59,006
The name is "My Love Garden". (Kuroiwa) My Love Garden?

75
00:03:59,073 --> 00:04:01,508
>> The idea is crazy, it's great!

76
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:04,445
(Old Man Toku) I had been considering the home, so it was a good fit.

77
00:04:04,511 --> 00:04:06,447
(Manami) I see, I see. (Tokujii) Hmm.

78
00:04:06,513 --> 00:04:09,450
(Kuroiwa) Please wait! People are dying.

79
00:04:09,516 --> 00:04:12,453
Why do we gather like this so carefree...

80
00:04:12,519 --> 00:04:15,956
(Manami) What's the point of crying alone at home?

81
00:04:16,023 --> 00:04:20,461
Everyone and I aren't family or anything.

82
00:04:20,527 --> 00:04:22,963
He is on probation and cannot be investigated.

83
00:04:23,030 --> 00:04:26,967
I feel like I'm going crazy because I can't do anything.

84
00:04:27,034 --> 00:04:32,473
That's why... I want to at least be by your side and protect you.

85
00:04:32,539 --> 00:04:34,541
(Kuroiwa) Huh...

86
00:04:36,043 --> 00:04:39,480
...But the types are all different, my love.

87
00:04:39,546 --> 00:04:41,982
(Manami) Oh, really?

88
00:04:42,049 --> 00:04:44,485
It's not a type or anything.

89
00:04:44,551 --> 00:04:48,989
Let's shine like this... As long as there's something that sparkles brightly →

90
00:04:49,056 --> 00:04:50,991
I say "I like it".

91
00:04:51,058 --> 00:04:54,495
(Kuroiwa) Is it okay? I am completely responsible for protecting those important people.

92
00:04:54,561 --> 00:04:56,997
(Manami) I'm watching over you. (Kuroiwa) Are you watching over me?

93
00:04:57,064 --> 00:04:59,066
(Manami) There's a surveillance camera.

94
00:05:02,069 --> 00:05:06,440
(Manami) I don't want to think about it too much →

95
00:05:06,507 --> 00:05:10,511
The culprit may be inside.

96
00:05:12,513 --> 00:05:17,951
To be honest, I think this is a very dangerous situation.

97
00:05:18,018 --> 00:05:19,953
So, based on that →

98
00:05:20,020 --> 00:05:23,023
I want everyone to decide whether or not to stay here.

99
00:05:25,025 --> 00:05:26,960
Well then, nice to meet you! (Kuroiwa) No, but...

100
00:05:27,027 --> 00:05:29,463
It's really strange that Manami isn't here.

101
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:32,966
(Manami) If I'm here, I'll definitely end up with someone.

102
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:34,468
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

103
00:05:34,535 --> 00:05:39,473
(Manami) Ah... I'm sorry, it's weird after all. I'll stay here.

104
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:42,476
(Kuroiwa) No, I don't like that.

105
00:05:42,543 --> 00:05:44,478
(Manami) You don't like it?

106
00:05:44,545 --> 00:05:46,980
(Kuroiwa) No... (EITO) But I'm like this →

107
00:05:47,047 --> 00:05:49,983
I don't want to stay with someone who violates public order and morals.

108
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:52,486
I mean, it's not good for the office.

109
00:05:52,553 --> 00:05:55,489
I'm just washing my feet.

110
00:05:55,556 --> 00:05:56,990
(Kuroiwa) That's right...

111
00:05:57,057 --> 00:05:59,993
(Manami) Emossan was the young head of Miura-gumi →

112
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:03,430
I finished my work and came back six years ago.

113
00:06:03,497 --> 00:06:04,932
>> Usu…｡

114
00:06:04,998 --> 00:06:07,434
Tsk. (Manami) Well, I'll be watching over you.

115
00:06:07,501 --> 00:06:08,936
(Emoto) Usu.

116
00:06:09,002 --> 00:06:11,004
(Manami) Nice to meet you.

117
00:06:15,008 --> 00:06:17,511
(Kiyosumi's voice) Hey, look carefully...

118
00:06:20,013 --> 00:06:22,950
(Sound of filling in with a pen)

119
00:06:23,016 --> 00:06:25,452
Wow! hey hey….

120
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:27,287
Keep an eye on me. (Kuroiwa) Huh?

121
00:06:27,321 --> 00:06:29,456
>> Director Takamine hasn't come yet, has he?

122
00:06:29,523 --> 00:06:32,459
(Kuroiwa) Is it that scary? I'm sure it's a career group.

123
00:06:32,526 --> 00:06:34,461
>> There's nothing scary about you.

124
00:06:34,528 --> 00:06:37,464
If you make a mistake, you'll keep stuffing it up until you can't remember it anymore.

125
00:06:37,531 --> 00:06:39,967
That's what I did for a year when I was 50 →

126
00:06:40,033 --> 00:06:41,969
I don't remember much of it. (Kuroiwa) That's scary.

127
00:06:42,035 --> 00:06:44,471
>> Ah, let's learn something about Tanizaki.

128
00:06:44,538 --> 00:06:47,474
That blank year is coming to me again.

129
00:06:47,541 --> 00:06:50,978
\I won't pack that much. / I'll pack it. He's sneaky...

130
00:06:51,044 --> 00:06:53,046
Peak management officer!

131
00:06:55,549 --> 00:06:58,485
(Kiyosumi) Thank you for your hard work...

132
00:06:58,552 --> 00:07:01,989
(Takamine) Regarding the 10 murders that occurred in Tokyo the other day.

133
00:07:02,055 --> 00:07:03,423
(Kiyosumi) Yeah.

134
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:06,426
In all three cases, we were able to arrest the perpetrators.

135
00:07:06,493 --> 00:07:08,929
(Kiyosumi) Oh, are you already there? You're early. As expected.

136
00:07:08,996 --> 00:07:13,433
In those three cases... the perpetrators had something in common.

137
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:18,005
They all received instructions from a person named Aichan.

138
00:07:21,008 --> 00:07:22,943
Did you know?

139
00:07:23,010 --> 00:07:26,947
(Takamine's voice) Apparently there were two murders involving Ai-chan before.

140
00:07:27,014 --> 00:07:30,017
What these two incidents have in common...

141
00:07:31,518 --> 00:07:34,021
There's one more thing, right?

142
00:07:41,028 --> 00:07:44,965
The two victims were sex friends of detectives from the First Investigative Division... or should I say sex friends →

143
00:07:45,032 --> 00:07:46,967
It is believed that they were in a romantic relationship →

144
00:07:47,034 --> 00:07:49,036
So….

145
00:07:51,038 --> 00:07:53,040
Manami Tanizaki.

146
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:56,543
She also becomes a suspect.

147
00:08:04,017 --> 00:08:06,854
(Erasaki) Also, ripe kabosu. (Kuroiwa) Do you sell them?

148
00:08:07,321 --> 00:08:09,756
Isn't lemon okay? (Erasaki) Ah, no way.

149
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:12,259
Tequila must be made with ripe kabosu!

150
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:13,760
(Kuroiwa) I don't know.

151
00:08:13,827 --> 00:08:16,763
>> Also, milky lotion! The one I'm doing the commercial for.

152
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:18,765
(Kuroiwa) That place, deep in the mountains→

153
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:20,767
There are no supermarkets, so there are limits.

154
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:23,770
>>If your skin gets rough, your fans will be sad.

155
00:08:23,837 --> 00:08:26,273
Well, Kuroiwa-kun doesn't have any fans →

156
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:28,775
I don't think I understand.

157
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:30,777
(Kuroiwa) Definitely write bad things on the internet.

158
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:33,280
(Monitor) It's bad for a detective to slander someone.

159
00:08:33,347 --> 00:08:34,715
I was surprised!

160
00:08:34,781 --> 00:08:38,218
(Monitor) Good work! (Manami) Is everyone getting along?

161
00:08:38,285 --> 00:08:40,721
(Erasaki) Something like a game master!

162
00:08:40,787 --> 00:08:42,723
(Wanibuchi) Is it really a death game!?

163
00:08:42,789 --> 00:08:44,725
(Kuroiwa) Please don't get excited.

164
00:08:44,791 --> 00:08:46,226
>> Hey, it's too messy here!

165
00:08:46,293 --> 00:08:48,729
I can hear weird vocal exercises coming from next door and it's the worst.

166
00:08:48,795 --> 00:08:51,231
(Wanibuchi) Just leave it there~ I'm going to lose my temper!

167
00:08:51,298 --> 00:08:52,733
(Monitor) (Iori) Only because it's true.

168
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:55,235
(Monitor) (Iori) You're not a kid, so don't fight.

169
00:08:55,302 --> 00:08:56,737
Sister...

170
00:08:56,803 --> 00:08:58,739
(Monitor) That's right! (Manami) Iori is right.

171
00:08:58,805 --> 00:09:01,241
(Monitor) It's a great opportunity, so please everyone get along.

172
00:09:01,308 --> 00:09:02,743
(Kuroiwa) Positive interpretation…｡

173
00:09:02,809 --> 00:09:04,745
(Monitor) How can we (Manami) become friends?

174
00:09:04,811 --> 00:09:08,315
(Erasaki) Are you going to drink? Cheers to save the world!

175
00:09:09,816 --> 00:09:11,752
(Sakatani) Are you the sake dregs next door?

176
00:09:11,818 --> 00:09:14,254
The smell has come all the way here and the grass can't grow.

177
00:09:14,321 --> 00:09:16,823
(Kuroiwa) Huh? Something is increasing. >> Ha~!

178
00:09:18,325 --> 00:09:19,760
(Monitor) (Yuriko) Well then, let's play a game →

179
00:09:19,826 --> 00:09:22,763
The person who told the story that most resonated with everyone was →

180
00:09:22,829 --> 00:09:25,265
Would you like a quiet and spacious room?

181
00:09:25,332 --> 00:09:26,767
That's burning!

182
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:28,268
(Manami) I wonder if there was a room like that...

183
00:09:28,335 --> 00:09:31,271
>> Well then, Manami-chan, the question is. (Manami) Huh?

184
00:09:31,338 --> 00:09:36,209
(Monitor) So, what's the most exciting situation you've ever been in?

185
00:09:36,276 --> 00:09:38,211
>> Huh? As expected, everyone →

186
00:09:38,278 --> 00:09:41,214
I think it's different because I'm a celebrity.

187
00:09:41,281 --> 00:09:42,783
(Wanibuchi: Sakatani) Tsk.

188
00:09:44,284 --> 00:09:47,220
(Erasaki) Emossan was just released from prison, right?

189
00:09:47,287 --> 00:09:50,223
No, it's difficult.

190
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:53,226
Even when I did it right before sending a message to another group →

191
00:09:53,293 --> 00:09:56,229
I thought I might die, but it felt so good...

192
00:09:56,296 --> 00:09:58,231
(Kuroiwa) No one sympathizes with that.

193
00:09:58,298 --> 00:10:00,233
(Erasaki) No, but I kind of understand.

194
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:03,236
Because life and sex are closely connected →

195
00:10:03,303 --> 00:10:07,240
We talked about hello at the temple where I was training.

196
00:10:07,307 --> 00:10:10,243
Ah, I'm a monk. (Kuroiwa) Is it okay to drink like that?

197
00:10:10,310 --> 00:10:12,312
(Erasaki) There are no such sects!

198
00:10:14,314 --> 00:10:17,250
(Kuroiwa) 《Wait, could this be...》

199
00:10:17,317 --> 00:10:19,753
《Let My Loves tell me about their backgrounds→

200
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:22,255
Waiting for Bolo to come out...? 》

201
00:10:22,322 --> 00:10:25,826
《Manami-san, I will behave well》

202
00:10:27,327 --> 00:10:30,764
(Monitor) (Cheers)

203
00:10:30,831 --> 00:10:34,701
Don't drink too much, you pervert aristocrat.

204
00:10:34,768 --> 00:10:38,705
(Manami) It's so satisfying to see all the men I like here.

205
00:10:38,772 --> 00:10:41,208
>>But it makes sense.

206
00:10:41,274 --> 00:10:44,211
It seems like it would be easier to do things if we were all in one place.

207
00:10:44,277 --> 00:10:47,280
Yes, whether you protect it or doubt it.

208
00:10:49,783 --> 00:10:51,785
(sipping sound)

209
00:10:54,788 --> 00:10:58,725
What is life and sex?

210
00:10:58,792 --> 00:11:01,228
I'm sure there may be.

211
00:11:01,294 --> 00:11:04,731
Hit by an occupation army car...

212
00:11:04,798 --> 00:11:06,733
(Monitor) (Tokujii) When I was about to die...

213
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,735
How old is this person? Three digits, right?

214
00:11:08,802 --> 00:11:10,737
(Manami) I'm sure he said that.

215
00:11:10,804 --> 00:11:13,240
You know, Old Man Toku's story is like a history textbook.

216
00:11:13,306 --> 00:11:15,242
It's interesting, isn't it?

217
00:11:15,308 --> 00:11:20,747
>> Later, when I met my ex-wife→

218
00:11:20,814 --> 00:11:23,750
Well, it was painful.

219
00:11:23,817 --> 00:11:25,752
(Yuriko's voice) People this age use the word "egui."

220
00:11:25,819 --> 00:11:29,756
(Manami's voice) I'm living in the moment, so no matter how old I am, I'll still be active.

221
00:11:29,823 --> 00:11:33,760
>>For me...it's quite difficult to be satisfied.

222
00:11:33,827 --> 00:11:36,696
The other side usually ends first.

223
00:11:36,763 --> 00:11:39,199
(Iori's voice) Don't worry! Sakatani.

224
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:42,702
(Manami) Sakatani-kun is in the tech category. >> Eh~ Is that what you mean by "tech"?

225
00:11:42,769 --> 00:11:45,205
(Manami) Being a technician has a double meaning.

226
00:11:45,272 --> 00:11:46,706
(Monitor) (EITO) As expected...

227
00:11:46,773 --> 00:11:49,276
I think the best time is when I do it with Manami-chan.

228
00:11:50,277 --> 00:11:53,213
(Manami) Yes, E-chan, you're the winner!

229
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,215
>> It's a bit...

230
00:11:55,282 --> 00:11:58,785
Kuroiwa-kun, why does your face always look grim?

231
00:12:00,287 --> 00:12:12,232
♪～

232
00:12:12,299 --> 00:12:14,301
(Kuroiwa) Um...

233
00:12:16,803 --> 00:12:18,738
Are you my love?

234
00:12:18,805 --> 00:12:21,241
